Official Nautilus GitHub repository from which this project is forked from.

http://osdir.com/ml/nautilus-list/2011-01/msg00021.html

E-mail to a Nautilus developer by a dude who wanted to port it a couple of years ago.


http://www.computerworld.com/s/article/9227318/Microsoft_dumps_Aero_UI_in_Windows_8_Metro_izes_desktop

News article which shows the new minimalist Windows 8 UI.


https://developers.google.com/drive/branding

Google Developers' site for Google Drive.


https://www.dropbox.com/developers/reference/branding

Dropbox Developers' site for Dropbox.

http://portableapps.com/development

Official PortableApps.com development page for Nautilus Portable.


In Closing
==========

So if you hate the new Windows 8, Windows Explorer (or just Windows Explorer in general) this is the project for you and I hope
to see some contributers other than me and my friend in the near future.

-Inferno986return-



